sais
------------------------------------------
sais is a very simple and small library that provides an implementation of the
induced sorting [1] based suffix array construction algorithm. The algorithm
runs in O(n) worst-case time, and MAX(2n, 4k) worst-case extra working space,
where n and k are the length of the input string and the number of alphabets.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.0.7-1
  libsais-devel-2.4.1-1bl1
  libsais2-2.4.1-1bl1
  pkg-config-1.6.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.14.5-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-7.4.0-1
  ninja-1.9.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://sites.google.com/site/yuta256/

Canonical download:
  https://sites.google.com/site/yuta256/sais-2.4.1.zip

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack sais-2.4.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./sais-2.4.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/sais-2.4.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/sais-2.4.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsais2-2.4.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsais-devel-2.4.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(sais)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/sais.README
  /usr/share/doc/sais/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/sais/README

(libsais2)
  /usr/bin/cygsais-2.dll

(libsais-devel)
  /usr/include/sais.h
  /usr/include/sais.hxx
  /usr/lib/libsais.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libsais.pc

